oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: City Lumber Company
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the office of the City Lumber Company. Two men and a woman are standing around a counter. City Lumber Company was started in 1903 to act as a retail and wholesale outlet for longleaf yellow pine produced by Mississippi and Louisiana sawmills
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Offices; Lumber industry
